<IMG SRC="http://www.infomrt.com/screenshots/test2.gif"></A></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ujantisconstanceeorle.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jantis ConstanceEorle</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_bluespot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Moo</span><br>  Posts: 64<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(10/20/01 11:53:04 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=50.topic&index=12>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.warghoul.com/images/CoSS/jantis_head_ez.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Roleplaying without PvP?</span><hr size=1> I agree with Vachir, to a degree.  I do not believe fighting always has to be a part of roleplaying, but there are some scenarios where it gets trite and circular when the only 'response' you can do between two groups of people that oppose each other is fill the shout channel with meaningless taunts.  I think there are many possible responses, but there comes a time when fighting becomes a part of the roleplaying, and /duel just doesn't cut it.<br>
<br>
Five evils come across Seven goodies and start to taunt and banter with each other.  That is as far as it can go without PvP.  With duel, there are no group strategies that can be used, and two people will be left out.  The time spent figuring out (ooc) who should fight whom removes the roleplaying element even further and if one side refuses the duel it is a big /yawn.  Nobody is going to give in or back down through /shout or /say banter so it grows tiresome.<br>
<br>
Just because some people (it isn't always 12 year olds, in fact most of them are 20-40 year olds that have the mentality of 12 year olds) don't know how to properly control themselves in a roleplaying situation does not mean PvP is bad.  <br>
<br>
Personally, I think PvP is something that should be a switch that you can turn off and on as you wish (though not while in combat).  GMs do this all of the time when doing quests, why shouldn't we be able to?  Just put a trigger that doesn't allow you to turn it off if someone is attacking you and you won't have people abusing it.  Or what the heck... why not?  If you don't want to die, then just let us turn it off an on any time we want.  How would this be an abuse?  It would allow for US to choose when we wish to be in combat.<br>
<br>
But it is completely un-realistic to have a gnome run into a group of ogres and 'banter' with them without any fear of being whacked.  It is also boring as get out to just hear threats and taunts as some weak excuse at roleplaying conflict.  It isn't creative at all... it's been done a blue-zillion time before all in the same way.  I wouldn't even have a problem with them making the 'home zones' of a race at least PvP to all races considered enemies.  That way you wouldn't have halflings sitting invis on the newbie log in Nektulos where the worst anyone can do is 'verbally dance' with them.  What a joke.<br>
<br>
Maybe another idea is to have a PvP 'arena' part of each zone so that you don't have to run to the Arena every time you want to have an actual fight or resort to *yawn* duelling.  Mabye at least make each homeland zone PvP to any race considered an enemy race.<br>
<br>
Roleplaying without any degree of PvP is a war of words, and after a while people grow tired of seeing the same bullies yelling at each other across the playground.  Fight or shut up... <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <br><font color=#A62A2A>- </font><a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie>Firiona Vie</a><font color=#A62A2A> - </font><a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm9>OT/OOC Forum</a> <font color=#A62A2A> - </font><a href="http://www.firionavie.org/">Firiona Vie</a><font color=#A62A2A> - </font> <center><a href="http://www.firiona-vie.com/fvchat.html" target="_blank"><h3>Chat Room</a></h3></center> <br><br><br><br>Powered By <a href=http://www.ezboard.com/>ezboard®</a> Ver. 6.6<br>Copyright ©1999-2001 ezboard, Inc.</center></body></html>  